text: Prothinodes lutata is a species of moth in the family Tineidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1914. This species is endemic to New Zealand. ==References== ==External links== *Image of type specimen of Prothinodes lutata. *Citizen science image of Prothinodes lutata.
